messages.messageBody:
Thanks for the feedback. We live about a 12 hour drive away, so I am trying to decide when we should arrive and when we should leave. I think we will stay Sunday night and leave Monday morning.

Christy

SandraDodd@... wrote:
I think it's starting Friday afternoon and ending sunday with the whale-watch
outing.

Whether to stay Sunday depends on how far you have to go to get home, maybe.
I know there will be some people staying Sunday night, and it might be a good
time to talk *quietly* with some people.

I could be wrong, but I think both Kelly and Kathryn are busy with other
things today so I'm chucking out a guess.

Sandra

messages.messageBody:
I'm planning on attending the conference this year and am trying to
make plans. I know the schedule isn't done yet, but I was wondering
when will talks/activities begin? I assume sometime Friday, will it
be morning, afternoon, or evening? I'm trying to decide when I want
to arrive. When are most people going to be arriving? I don't want
to miss anything! When will the activities end? Should I plan on
staying over Sunday night?

I guess that is it. With my job and my husband's job we need to plan
early.

Thanks,

Christy
